# Routing — `expo-router`

File-based routing under `src/app/`. Group folders use parentheses:

```
src/app/
  _layout.tsx                  # Root <Stack> — token gate + businessId gate for work screens
  index.tsx                    # Redirect: /(tabs) if businessId else /(pre-work)/(tabs)/businesses
  (auth)/                      # sign-in / sign-up / verify
  (pre-work)/                  # optional group; shell is <Slot />
    (tabs)/                    # Bottom tabs when signed in but business not selected yet
      _layout.tsx
      businesses/index.tsx     # Businesses / NoBusiness picker
      profile/index.tsx        # Provider user profile (customer-style)
  (tabs)/                      # bottom tabs (queues, history, profile) — requires businessId
    _layout.tsx
    index.tsx
    history/index.tsx
    profile/index.tsx
  no-business/index.tsx        # Legacy → Redirect to /(pre-work)/(tabs)/businesses
  create-business/index.tsx
  edit-profile/index.tsx       # Token-only stack (accessible before business selected)
  change-password/index.tsx
  change-language/index.tsx
  contact-us/index.tsx
  how-payments-work/index.tsx
  business-details/index.tsx
  services/index.tsx
  booking-info/[id]/index.tsx  # presentation: "containedModal"
  ...
```

## Auth gates

Unlike `xizmat-app-mobile` (single token gate), providers have:

1. **`token`** — authenticated user; unauthenticated routes use `(auth)`.
2. **`businessId`** — required for `(tabs)` (queues/history/**business profile**), services, business-details, edit-business, create-service…

**Signed in, no `businessId`** (no business selected / empty list): **`/(pre-work)/(tabs)`** — **Businesses** + **Profile** tabs. `/` redirects here (or straight to **`/(tabs)`** if `businessId` is set).

Screens that must work **before** a business is selected live under **`guard={!!token}`** **outside** `guard={!!businessId}`**: `create-business`, `(pre-work)`, `no-business`, `edit-profile`, `change-password`, `change-language`, `contact-us`, `how-payments-work`, booking modal, root `index`, etc.

```tsx
<Stack.Protected guard={!!token}>
  <Stack.Screen name="index" ... />
  <Stack.Screen name="(pre-work)" ... />
  <Stack.Screen name="create-business/index" ... />
  <Stack.Screen name="no-business/index" ... />
  <Stack.Screen name="edit-profile/index" />
  <Stack.Screen name="change-password/index" />
  <Stack.Screen name="change-language/index" />
  <Stack.Screen name="contact-us/index" />
  <Stack.Screen name="how-payments-work/index" />
  <Stack.Protected guard={!!businessId}>
    <Stack.Screen name="(tabs)" ... />
    <Stack.Screen name="services/index" ... />
    {/* other work screens */}
  </Stack.Protected>
</Stack.Protected>
```

When a provider has 0 businesses, **Businesses** tab shows **`NoBusiness`**. Creating a business (**`createBusiness`**) keeps them in pre-work until **`setBusinessId`**. Selecting a business → **`/(tabs)`** (queues).

## Screen conventions

- Every `app/<route>/index.tsx` is a **thin shell** importing a `Feature` from `@/features`.
- The root `_layout.tsx` registers fonts, splash screen, Apollo, gesture handler,
  bottom-sheet provider, keyboard provider, notification handler, and `<Toaster />`.
- Custom header back button is configured in `screenOptions.headerLeft` (outlined
  circular Button with `ChevronLeftIcon`). Keep new screens consistent.
- Modals: set `presentation: "containedModal"` on screens that should slide in.

## i18n — `i18next` + `react-i18next`

- Languages: `en`, `uz`, `ru` (default `en`). Locales in `src/i18n/locales/*.json`.
- Init in `src/i18n/index.ts`; user preference comes from `useAuthStore.language`,
  fallback to device locale via `expo-localization`.
- Inside components: `const { t } = useTranslation();` then `t('feature.key')`.
- **Keys are dot-namespaced** by feature: `queues.title`, `bookings.empty.title`,
  `business.create_button`, `actions.save`.
- **`user_profile.*`** — signed-in provider profile (pre-business tabs); **`profile.*`** —
  language labels shared with Business profile; **`tab_bar.businesses`** —
  Businesses tab label.
- **Backend errors** are namespaced under `graphql_errors.*` and the key is exactly
  the backend's `BadRequestException('camelCaseKey')` message. Adding a new backend
  error → add `graphql_errors.camelCaseKey` to **all three** locale files **AND**
  to the customer app's locale files if the error can be raised there too.
- Date helpers use `dayjs` with `uz-latn` locale loaded in `app/_layout.tsx`.
